OCR models and native OCR binary
--------------------------------
- eng.traineddata (Tesseract English model) — Apache License 2.0
  Bundled at worker/open_pdf_worker/tessdata/eng.traineddata and included
  in the frozen worker package. Runtime model downloads are disabled.
- Tesseract OCR binary — Apache License 2.0
  Resolved at runtime from the installation environment (or TESSERACT_CMD).
  Platform installers (Tickets 9/10) must ship a compatible binary with the
  application; the conversion release gate assumes it is available offline.

Desktop application (Flutter)
-----------------------------
Pinned via app/pubspec.lock. Direct production dependencies include:
- flutter (SDK)
- pdfrx — PDF rendering
- file_selector — native file dialogs
- url_launcher — reveal/open saved workbooks
- path, cupertino_icons

Build tooling (not shipped to end users)
----------------------------------------
- pyinstaller 6.21.0 — GPL-compatible / commercial terms as upstream
- pytest 8.3.4 — MIT License

No heavier conversion engines (for example PaddleOCR or Docling) are
bundled in this release. Adding one requires measured corpus failures that
justify the package-size and maintenance cost, recorded in the release gate
report.
